There's a very easy way to do this. You can just specify an Environment. With the documented API calls this would be possible. It's also possible to use `jedi.api.environment.SameEnvironment()`, which is easy to use. 

The only thing that we might change is the default when no environment is given. Currently it looks for the "latest" Python. We could just switch to using the same Python. This is IMO not much worse. The consequence would be that if you were editing things like type hints in a Python 2 environment, autocompletion would not work. We choose the latest Python version to make everything work.

@micbou Would you mind if we changed the current functionality of using the latest Python to using the same environment? We've had quite a few complaints and I feel like I'm explaining this a bit to often. It would obviously be more intuitive if the same environment would be chosen. This change would only affect the default if `Script(..., environment=None)`.

Hi @mhoffmann10!

When the ajax call completes, that's when the update needs to be triggered on the table. Try this change to the code:

```js
$.ajax({
  data: dataString,
  type: 'POST',
  url: '<?php echo base_url(); ?>admin/updatesort/'
}).done(function(data) {
  if (data) {
    // add the data to the table here?
    $('table.dispatchsort').trigger('update',[true]);
  }
});
```

I'm not sure where the content of the table is being updated, but if it is missing it should be done immediately before the update is triggered.

If the entire page is being updated, then you'll need to make sure that tablesorter is initialized on document end or move the initialization code to the bottom of the page (immediately before the `</body>` tag).

