@jmswenski @jeffreydwalter Motion detection causes  an event, which will hit the EventStream which you can `.Subscribe()` to. However, the EventStream will eventually pause due to the standard "logged out for inactivity" metaphor (that also occurs in the web dashboard). The motion event will look something like:

```
event = {u'action': u'is', u'resource': u'cameras/4WA16B7M72***', u'transId': u'48946B7GA***!41***92!1503***739902', u'from': u'48946B7GA9***', u'properties': {u'motionDetected': True}}
```

with the `u'properties': {u'motionDetected': True}` part being the most important.

Ideally there would be a thread that would keep the authentication alive, but the EventStream as it sits, is good for at least 10 minutes.

