@bjmc The trouble in this case is a matter of how intelligible the decorator itself is to developers working on the project. If you write this the less complex way, there's a chance that application itself fails (i.e. at import time) when a developer misuses it, which `wraps` doesn't change. Adding more complexity here allows for better errors to be generated, since they're custom exceptions rather than syntax errors for bad arguments to a decorator.
